==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
French ''[[queue#French|queue]]'', from Latin ''[[cauda]]''

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/kjuː/}}

====Homophones====
*[[cue]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#{{italbrac|UK}} A line of people, vehicles or other objects, in which the person or object at the front end is dealt with first, the one behind is dealt with next, and so on, and which newcomers join at the opposite end.
#{{italbrac|UK}} A [[waiting list]] or other means of organising people or objects into a first-come-first-served order.
#{{computing}} A [[data structure]] in which objects are removed from one end, called the [[head]], and added to the other, called the [[tail]], in an [[analogous]] manner to a queue in the sense above. This method of queueing being called [[first-in first-out]] is often abbreviated to [[FIFO]].
#{{computing}} A '''queue''' having the [[head]] and the [[tail]] at the same end; a [[LIFO]] queue, a [[stack]].

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[line]] (''US'')

